{
  "texts": [
    "One reason for this could be, in part, the unexpected insolvency of the CEX FTX in November 2022, which caused general uncertainty in the cryptocurrency market (Yaffe-Bellany, 2022) and compelled CEXs to improve the transparency in managing their customer funds in order to regain or strengthen their customer's trust (Li, 2023).",
    "The inception of CEXs and DEXs can be traced back to the early days of cryptocurrency trading.",
    "Centralized exchanges, like the infamous Mt.",
    "Gox (Greenberg, 2014; Mohan, 2022), established the initial framework for trading cryptocurrencies against traditional fiat currencies.",
    "While these platforms played a crucial role in the market's inception, they displayed vulnerabilities to security breaches, regulatory oversight, and operational limitations (Caliskan, 2020; Chohan, 2022)."
  ]
}